 efforts to restrain and manage such claims.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aChristian saintsxCultzItalyxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aLaityxCatholic ChurchxHistoryyTo 1500. 0aSanctificationxCatholic Church. 4aMedieval & Renaissance Studies. 4aReligious Studies. 4aWomens Studies.  acharity, gender, history of Christianity, European history, cults, lay, charisma, gender, authority, miracle.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065198008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2019 Englishz978311061017808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2019z9783110606195oZDB-23-DEG40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501740213?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501740213423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501740213/original  a978-3-11-061017-8  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-065198-0  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DEGb2019  aZDB-23-DGGb2019